data.description: Francis Phan is a product design leader, creative technologist, and San Francisco Bay Area music producer. Francis is a Rutgers Alum, earning his M.S. in Biomedical Engineering in 1994. He has a diverse background in media, advertising, eCommerce, and music technology. He is focused on building products that leverage AI to inspire and empower creators.    Francis is presently the Head of Product Design at Splice, a music creation platform and marketplace. Before his role at Splice, he made significant contributions as Yahoo's Director of Product Design for Ad Innovation, where he was responsible for steering product strategy and design for Native Advertising across Yahoo's expansive owned and operated portfolio.  Francis will take you on a journey through his process and methodology for innovation-driven thinking. Starting with his academic roots at Rutgers, he will illustrate how this approach has guided his career choices and shaped his contributions to product development. Furthermore, Francis will explore the dynamic interplay between AI-based technology and artistic expression, offering a glimpse into the exciting future of innovation and design
data.name: Innovator's Cafe: Alumni Lecture

data.description: AHGSO invites you to a screening of   Portrait of a Lady on Fire (2019) Dir. Céline Sciamma   Wednesday October 18, 2023 // 5:30 PM   Vorhees Hall, 71 Hamilton, New Brunswick Art History Graduate Lounge & via Zoom (registration)   Following the screening, a discussion will be led by Professor Jenevieve DeLosSantos.    Brittany, France, 1760. Marianne, a painter, is commissioned to do the wedding portrait of Héloïse, a young lady who has just left the convent. Héloïse is a reluctant bride to be and Marianne must paint her without her knowing. She observes her by day and secretly paints her at night. Intimacy and attraction grow between the two women as they share Héloïse’s first and last moments of freedom, all whilst Marianne paints the portrait that will end it all.
data.location: Vorhees Basement, Art History Grad Lounge
data.name: Film Screening: Portrait of a Lady on Fire
data.organizationName: Art History Graduate Student Organization (Graduate Organization)

data.description: Join us and learn more about the Master of Business and Science degree program. Enjoy light refreshments, a program presentation, and a lively Q&A. Faculty advisors and program staff will be on hand to discuss the program, academic and professional goals. This unique program combines advanced, STEM-based education with professionally guided business instruction—enabling graduates to step confidently and adeptly into the STEM workforce. The MBS degree provides - externship, internship, executive coaching, an alumni-student mentoring program, professional development, colloquium and more! Please register for this event here.

data.description: Celebrate the end of the academic year by joining Douglass staff, the Voorhees Choir, and fellow students for the annual Sacred Path Ceremony. One of Douglass' oldest traditions, the Sacred Path ceremony recognizes student achievement and fosters Douglass's unique community. Join your fellow Douglass classmates, alumnae, friends, and family as each class is honored with a symbol representing the different class years. After you receive your charm, head to the ceremonial fires on the sacred path to make a wish!  Students should show their pride by wearing their class year colors (first years wear white, sophomores wear pink, juniors wear red, and seniors wear black). Every student will receive a charm, a token representing her class. All Douglass students, family, faculty, and alumnae are welcome! Refreshments will be provided at Ludwig immediately following the ceremony.  *Students in Knowledge & Power will receive 2 points towards their Douglass event requirements*
data.name: Sacred Path 2024
